Hello fellow content marketers, if you’re like me, it can be incredibly overwhelming and intimidating to stay relevant when it comes to keeping up with all of the different content formats.

To help, I put together this guide to becoming a Multimedia Content Marketer. The article dives into:
:chart_with_upwards_trend: The rising trends of different content formats
:thinking_face: How to decide what types of content to produce
:hammer_and_wrench: The no-pro tool landscape and tool recommendations for creating multimedia content
:brain: How to have a multimedia content marketer mindset — so that no matter what new trends or content formats come your way, you’ll be able to embrace them like the pro that you already are :muscle:

Check out “The ultimate guide to becoming a multimedia content marketer” here :point_down:
<https://www.wibbitz.com/blog/the-ultimate-guide-to-becoming-a-multimedia-content-marketer>

I’d love to hear your feedback on the article as well. Let me know if there’s anything missing or that misses the mark! :pray:

Hi all! I was just recently hired for a Senior Content Manager role. During my interview process - I was asked the same question by multiple companies "What would you change about our current content strategy?" I feel like this is a trick question and I almost never gave a specific suggestion. My current employers loved my answer to this question so I decided to post about it on LI.

What do you think? Can you answer that question or do you need specific data to do so? Leave a comment and let me know! - <https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:6805517168541782016/>
